By Hussaini Hammangabdo, Adamawa government supported by the UNICEF have commenced the reconstruct of 80 schools in Guyuk and Fufore LGAs of the state. Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri on Thursday, at the flag off at Central Primary School Fufore said, 165 classrooms would be renovated through the intervention. In Fufore, the Governor pointed out that, the work involved construction and rehabilitation of 40 blocks of 80 classrooms and one parameter fence of 256 metres. In Guyuk locsl government also 42 blocks of 85 classrooms and three latrines for male and female pupils are to be renovated and sunk in Guyuk. Fintiri lauded UNICEF and other development partners for collaborating with the state government to execute the project. According to him, government is committed to compliment the efforts of the UNICEF and other donor agencies by ensuring that funds released for projects are judiciously used Dr Salihu Ateequ, the Executive Chairman of ADSUBEB, said the project would reduce class congestion, improve  hygiene condition  and security of pupils. The Chief UNICEF Bauchi Field Office, Mr Bhanu Pathak said his organization is poised to continue partnering the state government to achieve the sustainable development goals in education. 